UNITED STATES of America v. STAHLEY LAND AND LIVE STOCK COMPANY. STAHLEY LAND AND LIVE STOCK COMPANY v. UNITED STATES. Nos. 362, 363. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Sept. 23, 1930. See, also, 43 F.(2d) 366. Albert D. Walton, U. S. Atty., of Cheyenne, Wyo. P. W. Spaulding, of Evanston, Wyo., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Dismissed September 23, 1930, per stipulation.
